{"policy_id": "POL-2024-001", "type": "health", "title": "Individual Health Insurance Policy", "content": "INDIVIDUAL HEALTH INSURANCE POLICY\n\nPolicy Number: POL-2024-001\nEffective Date: 2024-01-01\n\nSECTION 1: COVERAGE SUMMARY\nThis policy provides health insurance coverage for individual policyholders. The coverage includes hospitalization, surgical benefits, diagnostic tests, and prescription drug coverage.\n\nSECTION 2: ELIGIBILITY\n- Primary policyholder must be between 18-65 years of age\n- Dependents include spouse and children under 26 years\n- Pre-existing conditions waiting period: 12 months\n\nSECTION 3: BENEFITS\n- In-network hospitalization: 80% coverage after deductible\n- Out-of-network hospitalization: 60% coverage after deductible\n- Annual deductible: $1,500 per individual / $3,000 per family\n- Maximum out-of-pocket: $8,500 per individual / $17,000 per family\n- Prescription drugs: Generic 80%, Brand name 60%\n\nSECTION 4: EXCLUSIONS\n- Cosmetic procedures not medically necessary\n- Experimental treatments not FDA approved\n- War or act of war\n- Self-inflicted injuries\n- Alcohol or drug related claims\n\nSECTION 5: PREMIUM PAYMENTS\n- Monthly premium due on 1st of each month\n- Grace period: 30 days\n- Late payment fee: $25 or 5% of premium, whichever is greater", "source": "cms_sample_1", "last_updated": "2024-01-15"}

{"policy_id": "POL-2024-002", "type": "auto", "title": "Comprehensive Auto Insurance Policy", "content": "COMPREHENSIVE AUTO INSURANCE POLICY\n\nPolicy Number: POL-2024-002\nEffective Date: 2024-01-01\n\nSECTION 1: COVERAGE TYPES\nThis policy provides comprehensive auto insurance coverage including liability, collision, and comprehensive coverage.\n\nSECTION 2: LIABILITY COVERAGE\n- Bodily injury liability: $100,000 per person / $300,000 per accident\n- Property damage liability: $50,000 per accident\n- Uninsured/underinsured motorist coverage included\n\nSECTION 3: COLLISION COVERAGE\n- Actual cash value settlement\n- $500 deductible required\n- Loss of use coverage: $30/day up to $900\n\nSECTION 4: COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE\n- Coverage for theft, vandalism, natural disasters\n- $500 deductible\n- Glass coverage: $0 deductible\n\nSECTION 5: DISCOUNTS\n- Multi-policy discount: 10%\n- Safe driver discount: up to 30%\n- Vehicle safety features discount: 15%\n- Anti-theft device discount: 5%\n\nSECTION 6: CLAIMS PROCESS\n- 24/7 claims hotline: 1-800-INSURE-01\n- Claim submission within 30 days required\n- Police report required for theft or vandalism", "source": "cms_sample_2", "last_updated": "2024-01-20"}

{"policy_id": "POL-2024-003", "type": "home", "title": "Homeowners Insurance Policy", "content": "HOMEOWNERS INSURANCE POLICY\n\nPolicy Number: POL-2024-003\nEffective Date: 2024-01-01\n\nSECTION 1: Dwelling COVERAGE\n- Coverage A (Dwelling): Based on replacement cost\n- Coverage B (Other Structures): 10% of Coverage A\n- Coverage C (Personal Property): 50% of Coverage A\n- Coverage D (Loss of Use): 20% of Coverage A\n\nSECTION 2: DEDUCTIBLES\n- Standard deductible: $1,000\n- Hurricane deductible: 2% of Coverage A (min $1,000)\n- All other perils deductible: $1,000\n\nSECTION 3: PERSONAL LIABILITY\n- Personal liability coverage: $300,000\n- Medical payments to others: $5,000 per person\n- Defense costs: Included in liability limit\n\nSECTION 4: EXCLUDED ITEMS\n- Flood damage (separate flood policy required)\n- Earthquake damage (separate endorsement available)\n- Mold (unless from covered water damage)\n- Normal wear and tear\n- Intentional acts\n\nSECTION 5: REPLACEMENT COST\n- Full replacement cost for dwelling\n- Actual cash value for personal property\n- 120% extended replacement cost endorsement available\n\nSECTION 6: ENDORSEMENTS AVAILABLE\n- Scheduled personal property rider\n- Water backup and sump overflow\n- Identity theft protection\n- Home business coverage", "source": "cms_sample_3", "last_updated": "2024-02-01"}

{"policy_id": "POL-2024-004", "type": "life", "title": "Term Life Insurance Policy", "content": "TERM LIFE INSURANCE POLICY\n\nPolicy Number: POL-2024-004\nEffective Date: 2024-01-01\n\nSECTION 1: POLICY TYPE\n- Term: 10, 15, 20, or 30 year terms available\n- Convertible to whole life until age 65\n- Renewable without evidence of insurability\n\nSECTION 2: COVERAGE AMOUNTS\n- Minimum: $25,000\n- Maximum: $5,000,000\n- Standard health class rates apply\n\nSECTION 3: BENEFICIARY DESIGNATION\n- Primary beneficiary: Name, relationship, percentage\n- Contingent beneficiary: Secondary if primary predeceases\n- Irrevocable beneficiary option available\n\nSECTION 4: POLICY FEATURES\n- Accelerated death benefit: Up to 50% of face value\n- Waiver of premium: If totally disabled\n- Accidental death rider: Double or triple benefit\n- Terminal illness rider: 30-day survival period\n\nSECTION 5: EXCLUSIONS\n- Suicide within 2 years (reduced benefit)\n- War or act of war\n- Aviation (non-commercial, certain conditions)\n- Criminal activity\n\nSECTION 6: CONVERSION OPTION\n- Convert to permanent insurance without medical exam\n- Conversion period: Within 5 years before term expiration\n- Age limit for conversion: 65\n- Premium based on age at conversion", "source": "cms_sample_4", "last_updated": "2024-02-10"}

{"policy_id": "POL-2024-005", "type": "health", "title": "Group Health Insurance Policy", "content": "GROUP HEALTH INSURANCE POLICY\n\nPolicy Number: POL-2024-005\nEffective Date: 2024-01-01\n\nSECTION 1: ELIGIBILITY\n- Minimum 5 eligible employees\n- 75% participation required\n- Waiting period: First of month following 30 days\n\nSECTION 2: PLAN OPTIONS\n- PPO Plan: Flexible provider choice\n- HMO Plan: Lower costs, network required\n- HDHP with HSA: Tax advantages\n\nSECTION 3: COVERAGE LEVELS\n- Employee only\n- Employee + Spouse\n- Employee + Child(ren)\n- Family coverage\n\nSECTION 4: EMPLOYER CONTRIBUTIONS\n- Minimum employer contribution: 50% of employee premium\n- Typical employer contribution: 75% of employee premium\n- Dependent coverage: Employer optional\n\nSECTION 5: WELLNESS PROGRAM\n- Annual biometric screening\n- Fitness club discounts\n- Tobacco cessation program\n- Mental health resources\n- Incentive credits toward deductible\n\nSECTION 6: COBRA CONTINUATION\n- 18 months continuation coverage\n- 29 months for disabled individuals\n- 36 months for dependent children\n- 2% administrative fee", "source": "cms_sample_5", "last_updated": "2024-02-15"}
